        dc:description           "Figure 7. Proserpinicaris wangpi sp. nov., scanning electron micrographs, holotype male. (A) Habitus, ventral view; (B) anal somite and caudal rami, ventral view; (C) antennula ventromedial view; (D) mouth appendages, ventral view; (E) distal tips of third swimming legs and exopod of left fourth leg, ventral view; (F) coxa, intercoxal sclerite, basis, and endopod of fourth swimming leg, anterior view. Scale bars 30 µm for (A), 10 µm for (B, C), 3 µm for (D), and 2 µm for (E, F)." ;
